sql:
SELECT name, description
FROM garment_types
ORDER BY name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- 'Most active tailor' refers to the user with the highest average edit count;
- 'Most recently accessed size charts' are determined by the latest access dates for each user and size chart combination;
- 'Edit count' is the number of times a size chart has been edited.

sql:
SELECT name, description
FROM garment_styles
WHERE style_id <= 1;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT size_chart_id) AS total_edited_charts
FROM size_chart_analytics
WHERE edit_count > 0;

external_knowledge:
- "most recently updated" refers to the latest version of each size chart;
- "most viewed and most accessed" refers to the size chart with the highest view and access counts;
- "modified by more than one person" means the size chart has been changed by multiple users.

- 'garment_type_id' uniquely identifies each type of garment;
- 'access_type' 'edit' indicates that the access event involved editing the size chart;
- 'access_count' represents the number of times a garment type has been edited.

- "disparity in measurements" refers to the differences between measurements in centimeters and inches;
- "all body parts" includes waist, hips, bust, inseam, and stature;
- "size range" refers to the range of sizes defined in the size chart, such as 2-4, 6-8.

- 'Most popular' refers to the highest number of views;
- 'Frequently updated' refers to the highest number of edits;
- 'After the start of 2023' means the changes were made after January 1, 2023.

- "Top 5 most frequently pruned size charts" refers to the size charts that have been edited the most;
- "Most active editor" refers to the user who has accessed these charts the most times;
- "Garden of frequent edits" is a metaphorical reference to the environment where size charts are frequently edited.
